    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah that's what i mean. but some people say the whole \"nonviolent\" focus was basically the only way that actually worked and that the more radical stuff just made things worse or distracted from the real goals. do you think the nonviolent approach was objectively the better way to go about it, or was it just more palatable for the people in power at the time?",
