      "content": "The effectiveness of nonviolence is heavily debated, as its success relied on harnessing public sympathy against brutal state violence. While nonviolent direct action was undeniably crucial for achieving landmark legislation, its adoption was also strategically calculated to appeal to moderate white allies. More radical approaches pressured the system by refusing to follow established rules, creating unavoidable crises that forced the mainstream to respond, even if that response was initially violent.",
